The Supreme Court of Appeal in Bloemfontein. Wikimedia Commons JOHANNESBURG - Self-admitted corrupt advocate Seth Nthai can no longer practise as an advocate following the decision by the Supreme Court of Appeal to strip him of his title.
Nthai was readmitted as an advocate after being removed for attempting to solicit a R5-million bribe over a decade ago. READ: SIU uncovers corruption in state attorney's office The Supreme Court of Appeal has now reversed that decision. It is citing a breach of ethical duty, counsel and standards of human decency. The court said the High Court had been far too receptive of Nthai's explanation in readmitting him. It has ruled that Nthai's actions constituted a serious crime.